"{\"uid\": \"foxnews.com-world-italy-cheers-faith-flag-milan-after-paris-woke-olympic-spectacle-sparked-culture-clash-experts-say\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 75, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92026 FOX News Network, LLC.\", \"from\": 76, \"to\": 104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 82, \"end\": 98, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FOX News Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quotes displayed in real-time or delayed by at least 15 minutes.\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Market data provided byFactset.\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Powered and implemented byFactSet Digital Solutions.Legal Statement.\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mutual Fund and ETF data provided byLSEG.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 308, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.901551097542657e-40, \"text\": \"ETF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Five-time Team USA Olympic skeleton athlete tells Fox News Digital about her battle to get a spot in the upcoming Winter Games after Team Canada withdrew from a recent competition, affecting her ability to earn points for qualification.\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999950382517, \"rank\": 3.9670012079265405e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 385, \"end\": 393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.514855533581161e-14, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}, {\"begin\": 468, \"end\": 479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9999980705320437, \"rank\": 1.895069642757978e-06, \"text\": \"Team Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris and Milan-Cortina delivered two sharply different Olympic spectacles, one that ignited culture-war backlash and another that leaned into heritage and national pride, a contrast some observers say mirrors the political paths ofEmmanuel Macron and Giorgia Meloni.\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 573, \"end\": 578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7304021828424547e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 825, \"end\": 839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giorgia_Meloni\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Giorgia Meloni\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giorgia_Meloni\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giorgia_Meloni\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic opening ceremonies rank among the world's most-watched cultural broadcasts, making them powerful stages for nations to project how they see themselves and how they want to be seen.\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 1030, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Paris tried to reinterpret tradition.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7304021828424547e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Milan showcased tradition,\\\" Hugh Dugan, an Olympic Truce advocate and former U.S. diplomat, told Fox News Digital, framing the contrast between the ceremonies as part of a broader debate over the role ofculture, politics and identityin the Games.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1070, \"end\": 1075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2553150744433363e-20, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.514855533581161e-14, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dugan described the 2024 Paris ceremony as \\\"a deliberately disruptive, decentralized, urban spectacle\\u2026 visually bold but polarizing,\\\" built around a narrative collage of modern France, diversity and reinterpretation of history.\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1343, \"end\": 1348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7304021828424547e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1495, \"end\": 1501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9989883468488173, \"rank\": 0.0009174401587929968, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said choreography and costuming \\\"often carried explicit social commentary,\\\" fueling debate over whether parts of the ceremony were intentionally provocative or ideologically driven.\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1730, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"OLYMPICS INTERNATIONAL SKATING UNION DEFENDS CONTROVERSIAL OLYMPIC JUDGING THAT DENIED AMERICANS ICE DANCE GOLD MEDAL  The Trocadero venue while the delegations arrive, in Paris, during the opening ceremony of the Summer Olympics, July 26, 2024.\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1977, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1904, \"end\": 1909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7304021828424547e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Francois-Xavier Marit/Pool Photo via AP)  The 2024 Paris opening ceremony, staged along the Seine, sparked controversy after a segment widely interpreted as referencing Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"Last Supper\\\" drew criticism from Christian groups and conservative commentators before organizers clarified the intent and apologized for any offense.\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2015, \"end\": 2017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.378477360989919e-16, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 2029, \"end\": 2034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7304021828424547e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.333553268503716e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2147, \"end\": 2164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5642283352308647e-29, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 2201, \"end\": 2210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999420599757533, \"rank\": 5.7943380374852815e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The moment became a flashpoint in France's wider culture-war debate over identity, religion and the meaning of public symbolism.\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2354, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9989883468488173, \"rank\": 0.0009174401587929968, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Conversation reported that the ceremony triggered a national discussion over \\\"woke ideology\\\" and France's cultural direction.\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2550, \"end\": 2556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9989883468488173, \"rank\": 0.0009174401587929968, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the performers who appeared in the Last Supper depiction in the 2024 Paris Olympics opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Tingshu Wang/Reuters)  Emma Schubart, a research fellow at the U.K.-based Henry Jackson Society, told Fox News Digital, \\\"The Olympics have become a stage for cultural politics as much as sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2703, \"end\": 2710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.181127773794815e-16, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 2713, \"end\": 2717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Darwin\", \"score\": 0.9841369932716164, \"rank\": 0.016111305085245987, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Darwin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Darwin\"}, {\"begin\": 2718, \"end\": 2726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Friedrich_Daniel_Schubart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Schubart\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Friedrich_Daniel_Schubart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Friedrich_Daniel_Schubart\"}, {\"begin\": 2764, \"end\": 2777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_M._Jackson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0921170420972773e-30, \"text\": \"Henry Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_M._Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_M._Jackson\"}, {\"begin\": 2792, \"end\": 2800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.514855533581161e-14, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She continued, \\\"President Emmanuel Macron's France leaned into progressive, 'woke' politics and post-national symbolism, while Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni's Italy emphasized heritage, tradition and unapologetic national pride.\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 3114, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2912, \"end\": 2927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 2930, \"end\": 2936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9989883468488173, \"rank\": 0.0009174401587929968, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3028, \"end\": 3042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giorgia_Meloni\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Giorgia Meloni\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giorgia_Meloni\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giorgia_Meloni\"}, {\"begin\": 3045, \"end\": 3050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9999999999145075, \"rank\": 8.485742678348792e-11, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These aesthetic choices reflect a widening divide over Europe's cultural and political future.\\\"\", \"from\": 3115, \"to\": 3210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Flagbearers Arianna Fontana and Federico Pellegrino of Team Italy walk in the parade during the opening ceremony of the Winter Olympics at San Siro Stadium on Feb. 6, 2026, in Milan, Italy.\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3224, \"end\": 3239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arianna_Fontana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arianna Fontana\", \"types\": [\"Q847400\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arianna_Fontana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arianna_Fontana\"}, {\"begin\": 3244, \"end\": 3263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federico_Pellegrino\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Federico Pellegrino\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federico_Pellegrino\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federico_Pellegrino\"}, {\"begin\": 3267, \"end\": 3277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.690891725049753e-19, \"text\": \"Team Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 3388, \"end\": 3393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2553150744433363e-20, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 3395, \"end\": 3400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9999999999145075, \"rank\": 8.485742678348792e-11, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Maja Hitij/Getty Images)  Dugan praised the Italian games, saying theMilan-Cortina Winter Gamesceremony highlighted \\\"tradition, harmony, co-existence and the Olympic truce,\\\" emphasizing heritage, landscapes and the athlete procession over political messaging.\", \"from\": 3401, \"to\": 3661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3446, \"end\": 3453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.7858034669327957, \"rank\": 0.26582305302806125, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He called the Italian approach \\\"panoramic, heritage-driven, classical,\\\" compared with Paris' \\\"maximalist, narrative-driven, experimental\\\" style.\\\"\", \"from\": 3662, \"to\": 3807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3676, \"end\": 3683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.7858034669327957, \"rank\": 0.26582305302806125, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 3748, \"end\": 3753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7304021828424547e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"IOC CHIEF LAMENTS 'DISTRACTING' NEWS CYCLE AHEAD OF 2026 WINTER OLYMPICS  Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni attends the Inauguration ceremony of the Olympic Torch Relay for the Milan-Cortina Winter Olympic Games at the Quirinale Palace, on Dec. 5, 2025, in Rome.\", \"from\": 3809, \"to\": 4075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3883, \"end\": 3905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Italy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Italian Prime Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 3906, \"end\": 3920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giorgia_Meloni\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Giorgia Meloni\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giorgia_Meloni\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giorgia_Meloni\"}, {\"begin\": 3962, \"end\": 3981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.786279141453334e-18, \"text\": \"Olympic Torch Relay\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}, {\"begin\": 4070, \"end\": 4074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9999999986580406, \"rank\": 9.52179219121121e-10, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Antonio Masiello/Getty Images)  Reporting on the Milan ceremony described it as a unity-focused event celebrating Italian culture, design and scenery while pushing past pre-Games tensions and highlighting the Olympic ideal of connection and peace.\", \"from\": 4075, \"to\": 4323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4076, \"end\": 4083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antonio_del_Pollaiuolo\", \"score\": 0.9999545055778867, \"rank\": 2.353224001746342e-05, \"text\": \"Antonio\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antonio_del_Pollaiuolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antonio_del_Pollaiuolo\"}, {\"begin\": 4093, \"end\": 4098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999997506329548, \"rank\": 2.485288121620544e-07, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}, {\"begin\": 4125, \"end\": 4130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2553150744433363e-20, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 4190, \"end\": 4205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_Italy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Italian culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coverage emphasized tradition and spectacle rather than ideological symbolism, with performances rooted in classical imagery and national identity.\", \"from\": 4324, \"to\": 4471, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dugan, who recently launched a Truce Compliance Index tracking how countries observe the tradition, argued the difference reflected two distinct philosophies about what Olympic ceremonies should represent.\", \"from\": 4473, \"to\": 4678, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Italian actress Matilda De Angelis performs during the Winter Olympics opening ceremony in Milan, Italy, Friday, Feb. 6, 2026.\", \"from\": 4680, \"to\": 4806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4680, \"end\": 4687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.7858034669327957, \"rank\": 0.26582305302806125, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 4696, \"end\": 4714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matilda_De_Angelis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matilda De Angelis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matilda_De_Angelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matilda_De_Angelis\"}, {\"begin\": 4771, \"end\": 4776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2553150744433363e-20, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \